@startuml
title Diagrama de Interacción - Comunicación Orchestrator

actor "Client" as CLIENT
participant "API Gateway" as GATEWAY
participant "Orchestrator" as ORCH
participant "Service A" as SVC_A
participant "Service B" as SVC_B
participant "Service C" as SVC_C
participant "Message Broker" as BROKER
participant "Circuit Breaker" as CB

== Escenario 1: Servicio disponible ==
CLIENT ->> GATEWAY: Request
GATEWAY ->> ORCH: Forward
activate ORCH

ORCH ->> ORCH: Resolver dependencias

ORCH ->> CB: ¿Service A disponible?
activate CB
CB -->> ORCH: CLOSED (disponible)
deactivate CB

ORCH ->> SVC_A: Llamada síncrona
activate SVC_A
SVC_A -->> ORCH: Response OK
deactivate SVC_A

ORCH ->> BROKER: Publicar evento
ORCH -->> GATEWAY: Response
deactivate ORCH

GATEWAY -->> CLIENT: 200 OK

== Escenario 2: Servicio con fallos ==
CLIENT ->> GATEWAY: Request
GATEWAY ->> ORCH: Forward
activate ORCH

ORCH ->> CB: ¿Service B disponible?
activate CB
CB -->> ORCH: OPEN (no disponible)
deactivate CB

ORCH ->> ORCH: Usar fallback
ORCH ->> SVC_C: Llamar servicio alternativo
activate SVC_C
SVC_C -->> ORCH: Response (fallback)
deactivate SVC_C

ORCH ->> BROKER: Publicar evento\n"FallbackUsed"
ORCH -->> GATEWAY: Response (degraded)
deactivate ORCH

GATEWAY -->> CLIENT: 206 Partial Content

== Escenario 3: Timeout ==
CLIENT ->> GATEWAY: Request largo
GATEWAY ->> ORCH: Forward
activate ORCH

ORCH ->> SVC_A: Operación larga (timeout: 5s)
activate SVC_A
note right of SVC_A
  Tardará 10 segundos
end note

ORCH ->> ORCH: Esperando...

note right of ORCH
  5 segundos: TIMEOUT
end note

ORCH -X SVC_A: Abort
deactivate SVC_A

ORCH ->> BROKER: Publicar evento\n"TimeoutOccurred"
ORCH -->> GATEWAY: 504 Gateway Timeout
deactivate ORCH

GATEWAY -->> CLIENT: 504

note bottom
  **Responsabilidades del Orchestrator:**
  1. Service Discovery: Ubicar servicios dinámicamente
  2. Load Balancing: Distribuir entre instancias
  3. Timeout Management: Evitar bloqueos
  4. Circuit Breaking: Evitar cascadas de fallos
  5. Request/Response Transformation: Adaptar formatos
  6. Authentication/Authorization: Validar tokens
  7. Rate Limiting: Controlar tráfico
  8. Logging & Tracing: Visibilidad
  9. Fallback Strategy: Comportamiento degradado
  10. Event Publishing: Orquestar eventos
end note

@enduml
